statistics.description: The angle of the fielder's route between his position at pitch release and his position when he started his fastest one-second window. 0 degrees is straight in to home plate, and +90 is towards the fielder's right.
statistics.name: Route to Sprint Speed

statistics.description: The angle of the fielder's route between his position at pitch release and his position when he started his fastest one-second window. 0 degrees is straight in to home plate, and +90 is towards the fielder's right.
statistics.name: Route to Sprint Speed

statistics.description: The vertical (z) distance between the position of the pitched ball at the front of home plate and the position the ball would have crossed at the front of home plate if it had moved on a straight line following its release trajectory.
statistics.name: Vertical Break

statistics.description: The vertical (z) distance between the position of the pitched ball at the front of home plate and the position the ball would have crossed at the front plate if it had continued on its release trajectory with only the force of gravity acting upon it.
statistics.name: Vertical Break Induced

statistics.description: The horizontal (x) distance between the position of the pitched ball at the front of home plate and the position the ball would have crossed at the front of home plate if it had moved on a straight line following its release trajectory.
statistics.name: Horizontal Break

statistics.description: The distance from the ball's position at bat-on-ball contact to the batted ball's position upon its return to ground level (z = 0).
statistics.name: Batted Ball Travel Distance (_z0)

statistics.description: The distance from the ball's position at bat-on-ball contact to the ball's position upon its return to eight feet above ground level (z = 8)
statistics.name: Batted Ball Travel Distance (_z8)

statistics.description: The distance from the ball's position at bat-on-ball contact to its position at first contact with the ground, wall, or a fielder.
statistics.name: Batted Ball Travel Distance (_zi)

statistics.description: The distance covered by the fielder between the ball reaching the fielder's glove and the release point of the subsequent throw.
statistics.name: Exchange Distance

statistics.description: The speed of the ball as it crosses the front of home plate.
statistics.name: Plate Speed

statistics.description: The angle formed by the initial pitch trajectory to the left or the right of the level yz-plane.
statistics.name: Pitch Launch Direction

statistics.description: The angle formed by the initial pitch trajectory above or below the level xy-plane.
statistics.name: Pitch Launch Angle

statistics.description: The angle formed by the initial hit trajectory to the left or the right of the level yz-plane.
statistics.name: Hit Launch Direction

statistics.description: The height of the ball as it crosses the vertical plane of the fence.
statistics.name: Ball Height at the Fence

statistics.description: The straightline distance between the projected landing position of the batted ball and the top of the fence at the same bearing.
statistics.name: Projected Distance of Ball From Fence

statistics.description: The time from bat-on-ball contact to when the batter exits the batter's box
statistics.name: Time out of Batters Box

statistics.description: A classification of a batted ball's projected contact with an outfield wall, either Unplayable (more than eight feet up on the wall) or Playable (less than eight feet up on the wall or within eight feet short of the base of the wall).
statistics.name: Wall Ball Classification

statistics.description: The time it takes for the batter to cover the first three feet towards first base.
statistics.name: Key Step

statistics.description: The distance covered by the batter during the first 1.5 seconds after the first three feet towards first are completed.
statistics.name: Burst

statistics.description: The number of revolutions of the ball between the pitcher's release point and when it crosses the front of home plate.
statistics.name: Revolutions Hand To Plate

statistics.description: The rate of rotation of the pitched ball around the horizontal axis (in the same orientation of a line between 1st and 3rd).
statistics.name: Inferred Backspin Rate

statistics.description: The rate of rotation of the pitched ball around the vertical axis.
statistics.name: Inferred Sidespin Rate

statistics.description: The rate of rotation of the pitched ball about the direction it is moving.
statistics.name: Inferred Gyrospin Rate

statistics.description: The distance between the location of the ball as it crosses home plate and the center of the strike zone.
statistics.name: Relative Strike Zone Location

statistics.description: The distance covered by the fielder between 1.5 and 3.0 seconds after pitch release.
statistics.name: Fielder Burst Distance

statistics.description: The distance covered by the fielder during the first 1.5 seconds after pitch release.
statistics.name: Fielder Reaction Distance

statistics.description: The difference between the total distance covered by the fielder during the first three seconds after pitch release minus the distance between where the fielder was at pitch release and where he was three seconds later.
statistics.name: Fielder Routing Distance

statistics.description: The ratio of the distance (in the horizontal direction) between the location of the ball as it crosses home plate and the center of the strike zone, divided by the horizontal edge of the strikezone. -100% would be a ball that crosses at the left edge of the zone, 0% would be a ball that crosses over the center, 100% would be a ball that crosses at the right edge of the zone.
statistics.name: Relative Strike Zone Location X

statistics.description: The ratio of the distance (in the vertical direction) of the ball from the center of the batter's relative strike zone as it crosses it divided by the vertical edge of the strikezone. -100% would be a ball that crosses at the bottom of the zone, 0% would be a ball that crosses over the center, 100% would be a ball that crosses at top of the zone
statistics.name: Relative Strike Zone Location Z

statistics.description: The categorical zone of the pitch's location at plate crossing based on the distance between its position at the front of home plate and the center of the batter's relative strike zone. These zones (from closest to farthest) are Heart Of Plate, Shadow Zone, Chase Zone, or OZone.
statistics.name: Attack Zones

statistics.description: Total distance the ball was thrown by fielder, including bounces.
statistics.name: Throw Distance with Bounces

statistics.description: An array of data about the point of intersection between the player's path and the ball's path (or projected point of intersection if they do not cross)
statistics.name: Intercept Batted Ball

statistics.description: The ratio of the last measured distance of the batted ball to the projected landing distance.
statistics.name: Hit Tracking Pct (%)

statistics.description: The distance between where the fielder was at pitch release and where he was three seconds later.
statistics.name: Fielder Jump Distance
